<Author>DDawnC
<Content>Even better the second time This was our second time visiting Amsterdam, and we chose to stay at the Sander again. The room we got was huge and newly refurbished- very nice. It looks like the one in the picture, with a wall of new windows, nicely tiled bathroom, big closet, faux fireplace, small sitting area, and spare twin bed. The breakfast was identical to last time- perfectly fine and tasty. The neighborhood is wonderfully quiet and a convenient jumping off point for getting to other parts of town. The staff made our stay very nice, too. We got help with bus routes, restaurant addresses, and taxi rides. There doesn't seem to be a bad person working there- they have all been very helpful and nice. On our second day there, we returned to find a small bottle of red wine and two glasses in our room, courtesy of the staff.We love Amsterdam, and we really like the Hotel Sander. 
