<Author>LJC1
<Content>Terribly dissapointed I had read good reviews of this 'hotel', but was terribly dissapointed when I arrived. It turned out to be a run down, none too clean, bed and breakfast establishment. My room was small and dim, with only a tiny light over the door, 2 tiny bedside lights and 1 even smaller desk light. The room was certainly warm, which was just as well as their was a howling gale coming in the window frame. The beds were clean and comfortable, the only really good thing. The shower room was clean enough, with plenty of hot water, but the air vent was disgusting. The furniture was rickity, I went to put my jacket in the cupboard, and took it out again as the cupboard was smelly. The breakfast is continental, and barely adequate. Why I say it is a bed and breakfast place is there is a bar, but the bar/lounge area and tiny reception area are closed and locked from 14.00p.m. in the afternoon, till 7a.m. the next morning, there are no staff in the hotel at all from this time, so what ever you do don't forget your room card, as it also unlocks the outside door, just make sure it works o.k. The hotel is certainly in a nice residential area, only 10-15 mins from the museums, and a further 5mins or so from the entertainment centre. This place is only sutiable for a very short stay, and not for the discerning traveller. 
